    "description": "FOLLOW-UP to safe-tx-oracle-v2-via-timelock.json. The previous batch swapped the 5 productId→shield mappings to V2 shields, but did NOT update CoverRouter._oracle, which still points to LuminaOracleV1 (0x4d1140Ac8F8cB9d4fB4f16cAe9C9cBA13C44bC87). The relayer reads the oracle address from CoverRouter.oracle() at startup and uses it as the EIP-712 verifyingContract when signing PriceProofs. If CoverRouter.oracle() is V1, the relayer will sign proofs against the V1 domain separator, which the V2 shields (which call LuminaOracleV2.verifyPriceProofEIP712) will reject. This batch wraps a single inner op — CoverRouter.setOracle(0x87B576f688bE0E1d7d23A299f55b475658215105) — inside TimelockController.scheduleBatch + executeBatch (minDelay = 0, so both run in the same Safe transaction). After execute, restart the Railway relayer service so it re-reads CoverRouter.oracle() and starts signing against the LuminaOracleV2 domain. Salt = keccak256(\"LUMINA-COVERROUTER-SET-ORACLE-V2-2026-04-09\"). Predecessor = 0x00.",
